• @rollacoaster “I see the way that artists are now and they're so much more personable, you're able to feel what they're going through a lot more because people are a lot more real. I love how social media and the music world have sort of collided. I did also have a huge passion for music growing up though, developing my tastes and going to concerts by myself. I think it’s hard for people to understand sometimes, by transitioning from social media to music. It’s as though a musician is suddenly switching to an entirely different genre.” 

Covering our Winter 2022 issue, @huddy reflects on the wider purpose of social media, finding his feet within the music industry and offers his own personal take on heartache ❤️‍🩹

Pre-order the issue now by visiting our #linkinbio 

@huddy wears @moutyparis, tank by @hanes, and his own jewellery

New work… @rollacoaster “I think there’s a degree of cynicism today where everything is ironic or tongue in cheek or satirical. We like to make fun of things but it feels like there’s a lack of earnestness. Is that the right word? I don’t know. But with The Notebook for instance, it’s unabashedly romantic. It wears its heart on its sleeve. If you put heart into a movie, that’s true humanity and that will transcend the test of time and last forever, right? Trends change and people change, but these stories stay enchanted forever.”

Talking on his return to the Enchanted franchise and the forgotten magic of romance, @jamesmarsden covers our Winter 2022/23 issue 🎬
